Y.P. Rai took over as the Chief Postmaster General, Andhra Pradesh Postal Circle, covering Andhra Pradesh and Telangana, on Monday.Dr. Rai did his doctorate in biochemistry from Jawaharlal Nehru University, New Delhi. He also graduated from the Defence Services Staff College, Wellington. He joined the Indian Postal Service in 1984. Besides holding various appointments in the Department of Posts, he also served in the Army and the Central Government in various capacities.Prior to this appointment, he worked as the Chief Postmaster General, Chhattisgarh Postal Circle.